22/04/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu met with Macedonian Defence Minister Jovan Manasjevski on Thursday (21 April). They discussed efforts the two countries are making towards NATO entry and stressed the importance of the integration process. The officials noted that the three countries that signed the Adriatic Charter -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- are co-operating not only militarily but also in the political sphere. (Albanian Daily News - 22/04/05)
